review_blob:
Yuengling Traditional Lager is a medium bodied, light amber lager. It starts with a very slight maltiness and finishes dry.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Yuengling Premium is a light straw colored beer. It's light, balanced taste finishes clean and crisp.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Lord chesterfield's Ale is a straw colored light bodied ale. It has a hoppy aroma that starts dry and finishes slightly bitter.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Java head uses expresso to give this stout it's distinctive coffee aroma and strong coffee taste with a hoppy bitterness. The totally black color reminds one of strong black coffee.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Stoudts Scarlet Lady ESB is an English style ESB. It has an amber/reddish color and a medium head. It starts with a slightly sweet maltiness and finishes with a hoppy bitterness and a slight floral aroma.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Stoudts Revel Red is a deep amber red ale. It has a distinctive hop aroma and creamy head that finishes dry with a hint of citrus hoppiness.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Stoudts Pumpkinfest Lager has a dark honey color and nice but short lived foamy head. I detected nutmeg and cinnamon with just a hint of vanilla and pumpkin. It finishes crisp and dry.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Stoudt Karnival kolsch is a German style ale that has straw yellow color. True to German brewed kolsches, Stoudts it is dry and crisp with just a hint of fruitiness. Where it falls short of an excellent kolsch is the slightly sour fruity finish.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Stoudts Winey Dog is Stoudts Fat Dog Stout that is aged in wine barrels for fourteen months. It has all the characteristics of Fat Dog but is extremely smooth. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Stoudts Fat Dog Stout is a rich dark a stout. It has a thick creamy head that combines an oatmeal stout with an imperial stout and finishes with a hint of coffee and chocolate.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Stoudts Fat Dog Stout (Vintages 2004 and later)

review_blob:
Pumpkin Ale for Zombies by Springhouse brewery is an excellent seasonal ale. The delightful amber color and nice head pair nicely with the spicy aroma and nutmeg/cinnamon overtones.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone
beer_name: Spring House Braaaiins! Pumpkn Ale for Zombies

review_blob:

aroma. One can taste pumpkin with some spice up front with a dry finish.

Moosehead Lager has a straw color and a light shortlived head. It's a light bodied dry crisp beer.

review_blob:
Dogfish Head's Punkin Ale is another fall seasonal ale that delivers a delicious aroma of spice and roasted pumpkin but falls short on real pumpkin taste. The dark amber color and foamy head are far more tempting than the taste.


---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Black Butte Porter is a good porter with a bit of hoppy bitterness. The roasted malt make for a good pint. It lacks the body that a truly well crafted porter possesses. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Old Fezziwig reminds me of Winter Lager. The has the same cinnamon and orange peel but differs with a sweeter and malty finish. Another nice winter brew.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Sam Adams Winter Lager starts with an aroma of spices such as cinnamon and a hint of orange peel. It's dark deep reddish color and thick head make this lager a tough one to put down.

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

The Hairy Eyeball is a great tasting winter heavy ale. The beautiful nut brown color, slightly malty start and smooth finish make this ale the perfect winter warmer. 

---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Great tasting seasonal beer. It is brewed with real pumpkin, so one can taste pumpkin along with cinnamon, vanilla, and pumpkin pie spices. It rich, golden amber color and long lasting head make for a very pleasing beer.
